    "causal_summary": "Eight /deep:* commands plus roughly twelve YAML assets reference the five old skill paths and skill: keys (the heaviest YAML carry dozens of path occurrences each). The command surface is independent of the skill folder and should stay stable, but every literal skill-path needs repointing. The repoint depends on the Python↔TypeScript {skill,mode} routing contract being finalized first (blocker B2) so fixtures and command bindings can be planned concretely. The per-mode required-input setup schemas and the \"do not transfer sibling defaults\" guardrails must survive verbatim.",
